column11: Manalkaadu Beach is located on the Jaffna peninsula, close to Point Pedro, and is administered by the Wadamarachchi divisional secretariat office. Wallipuram temple can be found close to Manlakadu beach. Manalkaadu beach is surrounded by a lot of sand dunes, and one part of the area is completely covered with cassuarina forest.

column8: Not a safe place to bath
column11: This is the northern most point in Sri Lanka. There’s a special area built to represent the unity of Sri Lanka. The beach around here is full of coral rocks and beautiful. There’s no designated parking area and you have to park beside the road.
This is a good beach in the north of Srilanka. This not crowded and not popular. You can see sand dunes around here.Manal Kadu in local Tamil language means Sand Jungle.
